727312f-b.title: Queens: Main Street - 37th Avenue
727312f-b.text:
Main Street; west side, between Thirty-seventh Ave. (left) and Northern Boulevard (right), showing an old 32 -story frame hip-roofed house said to have been built, according to the City Club Guide, at the end of the 18th Century. This building in 1923 was renovated, its front changed to brick and the hip taken out of the roof,substituting a flat roof therefor. IIt was then known as the Riesenburger Building and was No. 27 Main Street. It was demolished in 1933. This
is a set of two views.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727315f-a.title: Queens: Main Street - 37th Avenue
727315f-a.text:
Main Street, east side, north of Thirty-seventh Ave., showing in the foreground (No. 3O), a 2-story brick building bearing the sign "Join Our Hoosier Club." It was upon this site that the First M.E. Church was erected. This building was subsequently moved to Fortieth Ave., between Main and Union Streets, on the west side of the Armory on
the north side of the street.
1922.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.
